22/04/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg said Wednesday (21 April) that Bulgaria would support efforts by other Balkan countries to join NATO.
Saxe-Coburg pledged that Bulgaria, as a new member of the Alliance, would advance the "open door" policy at NATO's June summit in Istanbul.
In other news, Bulgarian Army Chief of General Staff General Nikola Kolev meets with his Romanian counterpart, General Mihail Popescu, on Thursday to analyse co-operation between the two countries' armed forces and to consider ways to bolster it.
They will also discuss issues arising from NATO integration.
(BTA, Rompres - 22/04/04;
BTA, Dnevnik, bTV, Mediapool - 21/04/04)
